14:09.240 --> 14:11.400
Anyway, Robin, this is...

14:11.560 --> 14:12.520
Carlos.

14:13.000 --> 14:14.560
- Oh!
- Oh!

14:17.920 --> 14:19.640
She's still talking to Carlos.

14:20.120 --> 14:22.240
I can still win this. I-it's not over.

14:22.320 --> 14:24.920
Okay, buddy. Time for the tough talk.

14:25.080 --> 14:27.760
Robin seems great, but let's look at the facts.

14:27.800 --> 14:29.200
You want to get married.

14:29.240 --> 14:33.560
And right now, there's a million women in New York looking for exactly you.

14:33.600 --> 14:35.040
But Robin ain't one of them.

14:35.120 --> 14:37.680
She's not just one of them. She's the one.

14:37.760 --> 14:40.760
Yeah, well, the one is heading up to the roof.

14:43.280 --> 14:44.640
What are you going to do?

14:45.480 --> 14:46.360
Nothing.

14:46.680 --> 14:50.120
It's a game. I got to just keep playing it.

15:27.400 --> 15:28.280
Ted...

15:28.360 --> 15:30.440
Hey, Carlos, can you give us a minute?

15:30.480 --> 15:32.440
Hey, no sweat, hombre.

15:33.160 --> 15:33.960
See ya.

15:37.640 --> 15:38.520
Robin...

15:38.760 --> 15:41.480
look, I didn't throw this party to set you up with Carlos,

15:41.560 --> 15:42.760
or the one before that,

15:43.160 --> 15:44.480
or the one before that.

15:45.760 --> 15:48.320
I threw these parties because I wanted to see you.

15:49.320 --> 15:50.720
Well, here I am.

15:52.040 --> 15:54.960
There's something here, look, unless I'm crazy.

15:55.440 --> 15:57.040
You're not crazy.

15:58.480 --> 16:00.080
I don't know, Ted.

16:00.120 --> 16:02.200
I mean, we barely know each other

16:02.400 --> 16:05.360
and you're looking at me with that look. And, it's like...

16:05.480 --> 16:06.240
Like, like what?

16:06.320 --> 16:09.120
Like, "Let's fall in love and get married

16:09.160 --> 16:11.440
and have kids and drive them to soccer practice."

16:11.520 --> 16:13.960
I'm not going to force sports on them unless they're interested.

16:15.560 --> 16:16.840
It's a great look.

16:17.480 --> 16:18.920
But you're looking at the wrong girl.

16:19.000 --> 16:20.600
- No, I'm not.
- Yes, you are.

16:20.680 --> 16:23.160
I don't want to get married right now, maybe ever.

16:23.240 --> 16:29.400
And, if we got together, I'd feel like I'd either have to marry you or break your heart, and...

16:30.240 --> 16:32.920
I just couldn't do either of those things.

16:33.400 --> 16:35.880
Just like you can't turn off the way you feel.

16:39.120 --> 16:40.200
Click.

16:40.400 --> 16:41.840
Off. Let's make out.

16:42.000 --> 16:42.920
What?

16:43.680 --> 16:45.800
What? That was the off switch.

16:46.000 --> 16:47.320
And I turned it off.

16:47.520 --> 16:51.400
I mean, look, sure, yes, I want to fall in love, get married, blah, blah, blah.

16:51.440 --> 16:55.480
But, on the other hand... you, me,

16:56.160 --> 16:57.480
the roof.

16:58.760 --> 17:00.240
There's no off switch.

17:01.120 --> 17:02.640
There is an off switch.

17:03.440 --> 17:04.720
And it's off.

17:05.200 --> 17:06.400
No, it's not.

17:07.400 --> 17:08.880
Yes, it is.

17:09.440 --> 17:10.720
No, it's not.

17:10.760 --> 17:13.680
Yes... it is.

17:27.319 --> 17:28.560
No, it's not.

17:29.360 --> 17:31.720
You're right. There's no off switch.

17:33.040 --> 17:35.040
God, I wish there was an off switch!

17:35.800 --> 17:37.040
Me, too.

17:42.120 --> 17:43.960
So, um...

17:45.200 --> 17:46.680
What do we do now?

17:49.280 --> 17:50.640
We could be friends.

17:50.880 --> 17:52.040
Oh...

17:53.360 --> 17:57.880
Look, I know it sounds insincere when people say that, but...

17:58.480 --> 17:59.520
we could.

18:00.320 --> 18:01.760
I don't know, Robin.

18:01.920 --> 18:03.560
I've made such a jackass of myself here.

18:03.640 --> 18:07.760
We start hanging out, every time I see you it'll be like, "Oh, that's right. I'm a jackass."

18:08.120 --> 18:09.440
You're not a jackass.

18:10.040 --> 18:12.240
Look, I'm sorry. I only moved here in April

18:12.320 --> 18:14.720
and I'm always working and

18:14.960 --> 18:17.960
I just haven't met a lot of good people so far.

18:19.280 --> 18:20.640
But I understand.

18:22.080 --> 18:26.560
Well, uh, maybe in a few months, after it's not so fresh,

18:26.640 --> 18:30.400
we could all, uh, you know, get a beer.

18:30.920 --> 18:31.960
Yeah.

18:32.880 --> 18:34.240
That sounds good.

18:35.600 --> 18:37.040
I'll see you, Ted.

18:42.000 --> 18:43.920
Or, you know, now.

18:47.480 --> 18:49.920
We could all get a beer now.

18:52.800 --> 18:54.040
I'd like that.

18:56.440 --> 19:00.600
My friends are going to love you... like you, you know, as a friend.

19:01.920 --> 19:03.120
Jackass.

19:05.760 --> 19:07.120
Unbelievable.

19:07.640 --> 19:10.640
That's just a recipe for disaster. They work together!

19:10.720 --> 19:11.560
Are you jealous?

19:11.640 --> 19:14.800
Oh, please. What does Carlos have that I don't?

19:14.800 --> 19:17.000
- A date tonight.
- Oh!

19:17.080 --> 19:18.920
Stop the tape. Rewind. Play it again.

19:19.200 --> 19:21.800
- A date tonight.
- Oh!

19:21.960 --> 19:23.200
I'm not sure I like her.

19:24.080 --> 19:25.560
Hey, don't you have a paper to write?

19:25.640 --> 19:28.080
- Dude, you're talking to the kid.
- I know it.

19:28.120 --> 19:29.640
I'm going to knock back this beer.

19:29.720 --> 19:31.520
I'm going to knock back one more beer.

19:31.560 --> 19:34.400
I'm going to go home. I'm going to write a 25-page paper.

19:34.480 --> 19:36.600
I'm going to hand it in and I'm going to get an "A."

19:36.640 --> 19:39.920
My name is Rufus and that's the trufus.

19:40.320 --> 19:41.640
He got a B-minus.

19:41.720 --> 19:44.600
But still, 25 pages in one night, B-minus?

19:44.640 --> 19:45.920
The kid was good.

19:46.440 --> 19:48.120
At least let me buy you a beer.

19:48.200 --> 19:49.720
Come on, I'll buy everyone a beer.

19:49.800 --> 19:50.800
I'll help carry.

19:55.800 --> 19:57.160
- You know something Ted?
- What?

19:57.200 --> 19:58.400
You are a catch.

19:58.480 --> 20:00.920
You're going to make some girl very happy.

20:01.080 --> 20:03.760
And I am going to help you find her.

20:04.120 --> 20:05.680
Well, good luck.

20:05.960 --> 20:07.840
I mean, maybe New York's just too big a town.

20:07.880 --> 20:09.840
I mean, there's millions of people in this city.

20:09.960 --> 20:12.920
How, in all this mess, is a guy supposed to find the love of his life?

20:13.000 --> 20:15.440
I mean, where do you even begin?

20:17.920 --> 20:20.240
Hi. Have you met Ted?

